- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper presents parallel versions of the algorithm for GPUs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with solving the Traveling Salesman Problem using a specific algorithm. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper presents a metaheuristic algorithm for optimization. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with solving a real-world optimization problem using a computational algorithm.
